pullRequest.body:
Main definitions:
* `def jacobiSym.fastJacobiSym (a : ℤ) (b : ℕ) : ℤ`
* `@[csimp] theorem jacobiSym.fastJacobiSym.eq : jacobiSym = jacobiSym.fastJacobiSym` 
* `def legendreSym.fastLegendreSym (p : ℕ) [Fact p.Prime] (a : ℤ) : ℤ`
* `@[csimp] theorem legendreSym.fastLegendreSym.eq : legendreSym = legendreSym.fastLegendreSym`

Also added tests

Please describe the algorithm in a few sentences here or in the module docstring. Also, is it possible to deduplicate the code between this file and the `NormNum` extension?

I don't know enough about metaprogramming in Lean to deduplicate the code (when I did a naive replacement I ran into a deep recursion error). I suspect the usual strategy is that there is a split between the computation rule and norm_num extension which additionally focuses on producing small proof terms. For example there is also a lot of duplicate logic between Nat.fastFib and NormNum/NatFib.
